    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>diced carrot</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> to the pan with the <strong>dried oregano </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for a further 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 4,
